The code below is an example of an infinite loop:

loop do
  puts 'Just keep printing...'
end

Q: Modify the code so the loop stops after the first iteration.

My A:

x = 0
loop do
  if x < 1
    puts 'Just keep printing...'
  end
  x += 1
end

LS A: 
loop do
  puts 'Just keep printing...'
  break
end